    <text id="R15110891T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>P. F. Howard writes Robert E. Lee in May, 1861, to notify him that arms are being
                    sent by train to Staunton for the use of newly enlisted regiments.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    COUNCIL CHAMBER,
                    <name type="recipient">Maj.-Gen. LEE,<lb/> Commander of Virginia Forces:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-05-14">May 14, 1861.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>The council desires me to inform Gen. Lee that an order has been given by the
                    Governor for a special train to Staunton to-night to carry the muskets and
                    rifles deigned for Grafton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully,</salute>
                    <signed>P. F. HOWARD,<lb/> Secretary of the Council.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
